    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-06T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-06T21:00:00-05:00" n="481"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d481">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1415: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-07T10:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 7, 1932—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 7—2:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>205. Following from American Consul General at Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“February 6, 4 p.m. Following telegram received from Bishop <persName
                                corresp="frus1932v03#p_OJA1">O’Shea</persName> at Kanchow, Kiangsi:
                            ‘Kanchow besieged by big Red army, please urge Nanchang send
                            succor’.</p>
                        <p>See Legation’s telegram of March 12, 11 a.m., 1930.<note n="9"
                                xml:id="d481fn9">
                                <ref target="frus1930v02#pg_93">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1930, vol. <hi
                                        rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 93</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>I am wiring Nanchang Government requesting protection for <persName
                                corresp="frus1932v03#p_OJA1">O’Shea</persName> and Father
                                <persName>Lewis</persName> (not registered, legal name unknown) who
                            are the only two Americans in Kanchow.</p>
                        <p>Nanking informed.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
